cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing and neural machine learning techniques to discover the structure of business processes from textual documents. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for process discovery. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques to induce the hierarchical structure of business processes. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with the retrieval of latent hierarchical structure from textual documents. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper addresses the challenge of process discovery in the context of Business Process Management (BPM) implementation in organizations.
